members.name: constant
members.doc: Creates a function that returns value.

members.name: curry
members.doc:
Creates a function that accepts arguments of func and either invokes func returning its result,
if at least arity number of arguments have been provided, or returns a function that accepts
the remaining func arguments, and so on.

members.name: currymethod
members.doc:
Like curry but if the method was executed as a static method it will accept self as the last
argument.

members.name: deprecated
members.doc: Warn when using wrapped func

members.name: flow
members.doc:
Creates a function that returns the result of invoking the given functions where each
successive invocation is supplied the return value of the previous.

members.name: fullname
members.doc: Get full name of a function: the module it is declared in and it's name

members.name: graceful
members.doc:
Creates a functions that returns the result of invoking the given function or None if
it raised an exception.

members.name: identity
members.doc: This function returns the first argument it receives.

members.name: noop
members.doc: This method returns None

members.name: rename
members.doc: Set a new name for a function

members.name: branches
members.doc: Iterates each path and value pair of the collection and it's descendent collections
members.signature: (collection: Union[Mapping[Union[Hashable, int], Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]], Iterable[Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]]]) -> Generator[Tuple[Sequence[Union[Hashable, int]], Union[Mapping[Union[Hashable, int], Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]], Iterable[Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]], ~V]], NoneType, NoneType]

members.name: delitem
members.signature: (path: Union[Hashable, int, Sequence[Union[Hashable, int]]], collection: Union[MutableMapping[~K, Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]], MutableSequence[Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]]]) -> Union[MutableMapping[~K, Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]], MutableSequence[Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]]]

members.name: getitem
members.doc: Gets the value at path of collection
members.signature: (path: Union[Hashable, int, Sequence[Union[Hashable, int]]], collection: Union[Mapping[Union[Hashable, int], Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]], Iterable[Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]]]) -> ~V

members.name: hasitem
members.signature: (path: Union[Hashable, int, Sequence[Union[Hashable, int]]], collection: Union[Mapping[Union[Hashable, int], Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]], Iterable[Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]]]) -> bool

members.name: leaves
members.doc: Like branches() but only yields non collection values
members.signature: (collection: Union[Mapping[Union[Hashable, int], Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]], Iterable[Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]]]) -> Generator[Tuple[Sequence[Union[Hashable, int]], ~V], NoneType, NoneType]

members.name: pick
members.doc: Creates a collection composed of the picked paths.
members.signature: (paths: Iterable[Union[Hashable, int, Sequence[Union[Hashable, int]]]], collection: Union[Mapping[Union[Hashable, int], Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]], Iterable[Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]]]) -> Union[Mapping[Union[Hashable, int], Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]], Iterable[Union[ForwardRef('Collection'), ~V]]]

members.name: setitem
members.doc: Sets the value at path of collection. If a portion of path doesn't exist, it's created.
members.signature: (path: Union[Hashable, int, Sequence[Union[Hashable, int]]], value: ~V, collection: Union[MutableMapping[~K, Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]], MutableSequence[Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]]]) -> Union[MutableMapping[~K, Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]], MutableSequence[Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]]]

members.name: to_path
members.doc: Converts value to a property path tuple.
members.signature: (path: Union[Hashable, int, Sequence[Union[Hashable, int]]]) -> Sequence[Union[Hashable, int]]

members.name: update
members.doc: This method is like set except that accepts updater to produce the value to set.
members.signature: (path: Union[Hashable, int, Sequence[Union[Hashable, int]]], modifier: Callable[[~V], ~V], collection: Union[MutableMapping[~K, Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]], MutableSequence[Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]]]) -> Union[MutableMapping[~K, Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]], MutableSequence[Union[ForwardRef('MutableCollection'), ~V]]]

members.name: chunk
members.doc:
Creates an iterable of elements split into groups the length of size.
If iterable can't be split evenly, the final chunk will be the remaining elements.

members.name: compact
members.doc: Creates an iterable with all falsey values removed.

members.name: find
members.doc:
Iterates over elements of iterable, returning the first element predicate returns truthy for.
Defaults to None.
members.signature: (comparator: Callable[[~T], bool], iterable: Iterable[~T]) -> Union[~T, NoneType]

members.name: find_index
members.doc:
This method is like find() except that it returns the index of the first element predicate returns truthy for
instead of the element itself.
members.signature: (comparator: Callable[[~T], bool], iterable: Iterable[~T]) -> Union[int, NoneType]

members.name: flatten
members.doc: Flattens iterable a single level deep.

members.name: group_by
members.doc:
Creates an iterable composed of keys generated from the results of running each element of iterable thru iteratee.
The order of grouped values is determined by the order they occur in iterable. The corresponding value of each key
is a list of elements responsible for generating the key. The iteratee is invoked with one argument: (value).

members.name: head
members.doc:
Gets the first element of iterable.
Defaults to None.

members.name: intersection
members.doc:
Creates an iterable of unique values that are included in given source and target iterables using hash() for
comparisons. The order and references of result values are determined by the first iterable.

members.name: key_by
members.doc:
Creates a dictionary composed of keys generated from the results of running each element of iterable thru iteratee.
The corresponding value of each key is the last element responsible for generating the key. The iteratee is invoked
with one argument: (value).

members.name: mean
members.doc: Computes the mean of the values in iterable.

members.name: uniq
members.doc:
Returns a duplicate-free version of an iterable, using hash for equality
comparisons, in which only the first occurrence of each element is kept.
The order of result values is determined by the order they occur in the
iterable.

members.name: uniq_by
members.doc:
This function is like uniq except that it accepts iteratee which is invoked
for each element in array to generate the criterion by which uniqueness is
computed. The order of result values is determined by the order they occur
in the array. The iteratee is invoked with one argument: (value).

members.name: create_empty
members.doc: Create a new mapping of the type of given mapping

members.name: is_dict
members.doc: Matches if value is a dictionary

members.name: items
members.doc: Mapping.items() for Mapping like objects that don't implement items()

members.name: map_keys
members.doc: Creates a dictionary with the same values as _dict and keys generated by applying modifier(key) for each key.

members.name: map_values
members.doc: Creates a dictionary with the same keys as _dict and values generated by applying modifier(val) for each value.

members.name: omit
members.doc: Creates a mapping without the omitted mapping items.

members.name: pick
members.doc: Creates a mapping composed of the picked mapping items.

members.name: create_empty
members.doc: Create a new sequence of the type of given sequence

members.name: initial
members.doc: Gets all but the last element of sequence.

members.name: last
members.doc: Gets the last element of sequence.

members.name: omit
members.doc: The opposite of pick; this method creates a sequence composed of the items that are not omitted.

members.name: pick
members.doc: Creates a sequence composed of the picked sequence items.
